subSubSection.paragraph:
Axis
: The surface of the axis is faintly longitudinally striated (
Fig. 21
), at intervals of 
0.26–0.33 mm
, and covered with minute tubercles ornamented with thorny projections (
Fig. 22
). There is no rounded pit on the axis at the position of each coenenchymal mound (
Fig. 21
).

Colour
: The dry coenenchyme is pinkish white, coenenchymal mounds and branch tips becoming darker (
Fig. 19
). Axis is white (
Fig. 20
).
